title: Meet Uganda’s mud wrestlers
description: The training is robust, with weightlifting and tactical exercises to prepare the wrestlers before they enter the ring. When they do, it’s a sight to behold.

title: International Criminal Court issues warrant for two Russian military leaders
description: The two military leaders are sought by the International Criminal Court in connection to alleged war crimes in Ukraine.

title: German police investigating suspected arson at Tesla site
description: The left-wing Volcano Group claimed responsibility for the attack, which knocked out electricity in several villages in the area.

title: Mr. Darcy’s wet shirt — yes, that one — is up for auction
description: Want to get your hands on Colin Firth’s famous wet shirt? The costume, from his role as Mr. Darcy in the BBC’s Pride & Prejudice, is now up for auction.

title: European court favors strong encryption, calling it key to privacy rights
description: The decision may ease pressure on U.S. social media companies to provide workarounds that would let law enforcement review encrypted messages.

title: Germany says missile conversation leak was a fluke, not a security breach
description: The leak happened after a German officer in Singapore used an unsecure line to dial into a conference call discussing Taurus missiles and Ukraine.

title: Soldiers, cops, cameras: China’s security state on show for Two Sessions
description: Chinese leader Xi Jinping isn’t brooking any dissent as the rubber-stamp parliament meets to approve his plans for the year. Security is extra tight across Beijing.

title: Chelsea’s Sam Kerr pleads not guilty to racially aggravated harassment
description: The Australian soccer star and Chelsea striker is facing trial in Britain over allegations that she harassed a police officer.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: U.N. team finds credible claims hostages were subjected to sexual abuse
description: Children in northern Gaza are malnourished and starving to death from a severe lack of aid, the World Health Organization said after visits to two hospitals.

title: The improbable U.S. plan for a revitalized Palestinian security force
description: The Palestinian Authority security forces are underfunded and unpopular, ill-equipped to take on the responsibilities Washington has envisioned for them in postwar Gaza.

title: Biden’s rift with Netanyahu grows wider
description: This week in Washington, the growing tensions between the White House and Israel’s Benjamin Netanyahu are coming to the fore.

title: China says economy will grow ‘around’ 5 percent this year
description: It’s shaping up to be a difficult year for the Chinese Communist Party as the economy slows. Leaders are trying to reassure investors, laying out plans to boost growth.

title: U.N. report: ‘Convincing’ information Hamas raped, tortured hostages
description: Expert team finds “reasonable grounds to believe” that sexual violence was committed on Oct. 7, but report stops short of an official investigation.
